## Why This Is Asked
Tests multi-cloud, multi-env orchestration, and robust gating. It probes backend scoping, provider aliasing, and policy-as-code integration in a realistic production-like flow.

## Key Concepts
- Per-env Terraform backends and state isolation
- Provider aliasing for multi-cloud deployments
- Policy-as-code gates (Sentinel/OPA) for prod safety
- Wrapper modules for consistent tagging across clouds

## Code Example
```javascript
// backend.tf (Terraform S3 backend per environment)
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket = "org-terraform"
    key    = "state/${var.environment}/terraform.tfstate"
    region = "us-east-1"
  }
}
```

```javascript
// Providers with aliases (multi-cloud)
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
  alias  = "aws"
}
provider "google" {
  project = var.gcp_project
  region  = var.gcp_region
  alias   = "gcp"
}
```

```javascript
// Wrapper module usage for tags
module "shared_tags" {
  source      = "./modules/tags"
  environment = var.environment
  cost_center = var.cost_center
}
```

```javascript
// Simple OPA/rego style policy (example)
package terraform.policy
default allow = false
allow {
  input.environment != "prod"
}
```

```javascript
// CI gate steps (high level)
terraform init
terraform plan -out=tfplan
terraform show -json tfplan > plan.json
# Evaluate plan.json against policy (opa or sentinel)
```
